# Supported AWS Services

The application supports cost calculations for the following AWS services, implemented in [src/aws_services.py](mdc:src/aws_services.py) and made available in the interface in [src/app.py](mdc:src/app.py):

## EC2 (Elastic Compute Cloud)
- Parameters: instance type, quantity, usage hours, region
- Support for on-demand instances
- Estimates based on approximate price tables

## S3 (Simple Storage Service)
- Parameters: storage amount (GB), storage class
- Support for Standard, Infrequent Access, and Glacier
- Calculations for monthly storage

## Lambda (Serverless)
- Parameters: number of requests, memory, average duration, region
- Calculations based on GB-second of execution
- Estimates including free tier requests

## Fargate/ECS (Elastic Container Service)
- Parameters: vCPUs, memory, usage hours, region
- Cost estimates for managed containers

## Additional Services
- CloudWatch (Monitoring)
- ElastiCache (In-Memory Cache)
- ECR (Elastic Container Registry)
- OpenSearch (Search and Analytics)
- Route 53 (DNS and Domains)

The application allows adding multiple resources of different services to create a total cost estimate.

